📄 SRS – SMART CAMPUS ASSISTANT 
1. INTRODUCTION
1.1 PURPOSE
This document specifies the software requirements for the Smart Campus Assistant, a lightweight web-based application designed to provide students with instant answers to campus-related questions.
The document serves as a foundation for system design, implementation, testing, and evaluation.
________________________________________
1.2 SYSTEM OVERVIEW
The Smart Campus Assistant enables students to ask natural-language questions related to campus information, such as schedules, locations, general information, and technical issues.
The system consists of a frontend interface, a backend service, and an AI component responsible for processing and generating responses. 
________________________________________
1.3 SCOPE
The system will:
•	Accept user questions via a web interface 
•	Classify questions into predefined categories 
•	Generate AI-based responses 
•	Provide fallback responses when confidence is low 
The system is designed as a functional MVP and does not include authentication or real-time institutional integrations.
________________________________________
2. STAKEHOLDERS
•	Students – Primary users who interact with the system 
•	Academic/Administrative Staff – Benefit from reduced repetitive inquiries 
•	Development Team – Responsible for building and maintaining the system 
•	Evaluator (Mentor/Examiner) – Assesses system quality and implementation 
•	System Administrator (Future) – May manage data and monitor system behavior 
________________________________________
3. OVERALL DESCRIPTION
3.1 SYSTEM ARCHITECTURE
The system follows a modular architecture:
•	Frontend – User interface (chat-based interaction) 
•	Backend (FastAPI) – Handles requests, validation, and logic 
•	AI Service – Processes questions and generates answers 
•	Data Source – Predefined campus information 
________________________________________
3.2 SYSTEM FLOW
1.	The user submits a question 
2.	The backend validates input 
3.	The system classifies the question 
4.	Relevant context is retrieved 
5.	The AI generates a response 
6.	The response is returned to the user 
If confidence is low → fallback response is returned instead of incorrect information 
________________________________________
3.3 ASSUMPTIONS
•	The system runs locally or in a demo environment 
•	Campus data is predefined 
•	No login is required 
•	The system focuses on campus-related queries only 
________________________________________
4. ACTORS
•	Student – Main user 
•	AI Service – Processes and generates responses 
•	Campus Data Source – Provides structured information 
•	Administrator (Optional) – Maintains system data 
________________________________________
5. USE CASES
________________________________________
UC1 – ASK A QUESTION
ACTOR: STUDENT
PRE-CONDITION:
•	THE STUDENT IS CONNECTED TO THE INTERFACE 
•	THE SYSTEM IS RUNNING 
•	THE AI SERVICE IS AVAILABLE 
DESCRIPTION:
THE STUDENT SUBMITS A QUESTION THROUGH THE INTERFACE.
THE BACKEND VALIDATES THE INPUT, CLASSIFIES THE QUESTION, RETRIEVES RELEVANT DATA, AND SENDS IT TO THE AI SERVICE.
THE AI GENERATES A NATURAL-LANGUAGE RESPONSE BASED ON THE CONTEXT.
POST-CONDITION:
THE STUDENT RECEIVES A GENERATED RESPONSE DISPLAYED IN THE INTERFACE.
EDGE CASE:
IF THE AI CONFIDENCE IS LOW → FALLBACK RESPONSE IS TRIGGERED
________________________________________
________________________________________
UC2 – CLASSIFY QUESTION
ACTOR: STUDENT
PRE-CONDITION:
•	A VALID QUESTION WAS SUBMITTED 
DESCRIPTION:
AFTER RECEIVING THE QUESTION, THE SYSTEM INTERNALLY CLASSIFIES IT INTO CATEGORIES SUCH AS SCHEDULE, GENERAL INFORMATION, OR TECHNICAL ISSUE.
POST-CONDITION:
THE QUESTION IS ASSIGNED A CATEGORY USED FOR FURTHER PROCESSING
________________________________________
________________________________________
UC3 – RETRIEVE INFORMATION
ACTOR: STUDENT
PRE-CONDITION:
•	THE QUESTION HAS BEEN CLASSIFIED 
DESCRIPTION:
THE SYSTEM RETRIEVES RELEVANT CAMPUS DATA BASED ON THE CLASSIFIED CATEGORY AND PREPARES CONTEXT FOR THE AI RESPONSE.
POST-CONDITION:
RELEVANT DATA IS AVAILABLE FOR RESPONSE GENERATION
________________________________________
________________________________________
UC4 – GENERATE RESPONSE
ACTOR: STUDENT
PRE-CONDITION:
•	RELEVANT DATA HAS BEEN RETRIEVED 
•	AI SERVICE IS AVAILABLE 
DESCRIPTION:
THE SYSTEM SENDS THE QUESTION AND CONTEXT TO THE AI SERVICE, WHICH GENERATES A NATURAL-LANGUAGE RESPONSE.
POST-CONDITION:
A RESPONSE IS GENERATED AND RETURNED TO THE BACKEND
________________________________________
________________________________________
UC5 – FALLBACK HANDLING
ACTOR: STUDENT
PRE-CONDITION:
•	AI RESPONSE CONFIDENCE IS LOW OR AI SERVICE FAILED 
DESCRIPTION:
THE SYSTEM DETECTS UNCERTAINTY OR FAILURE AND RETURNS A PREDEFINED FALLBACK MESSAGE INSTEAD OF A POTENTIALLY INCORRECT ANSWER.
POST-CONDITION:
THE USER RECEIVES A FALLBACK RESPONSE
________________________________________
________________________________________
UC6 – USE SUGGESTED QUESTIONS
ACTOR: STUDENT
PRE-CONDITION:
•	THE SYSTEM INTERFACE IS ACTIVE 
•	SUGGESTED QUESTIONS ARE AVAILABLE 
DESCRIPTION:
THE USER SELECTS A PREDEFINED QUESTION INSTEAD OF TYPING MANUALLY.
THE SYSTEM PROCESSES IT THROUGH THE SAME PIPELINE AS A REGULAR QUESTION.
POST-CONDITION:
THE USER RECEIVES AN ANSWER FOR THE SELECTED QUESTION
________________________________________
6. FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS
1.	The system shall allow users to input questions via a web interface 
2.	The system shall validate user input (non-empty) 
3.	The system shall classify questions into at least three categories 
4.	The system shall send the question to an AI service 
5.	The system shall return a generated response 
6.	The system shall display the detected category 
7.	The system shall provide fallback responses when needed 
8.	The system shall support predefined suggested questions 
9.	The system shall display error messages when failures occur 
10.	The system shall maintain temporary session history 
11.	The system shall allow clearing the chat history 
________________________________________
7. NON-FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS
7.1 PERFORMANCE
•	Average response time ≤ 3 seconds under normal conditions 
7.2 USABILITY
•	Users should be able to use the system without prior training 
•	Interface should be intuitive and minimal 
7.3 RELIABILITY
•	The system should avoid generating incorrect answers 
•	The system must automatically trigger Fallback Handling (UC2) for any AI-generated response with a confidence score < 0.8. This ensures that only verified, high-certainty information is presented to the student.
7.4 MAINTAINABILITY
•	The system should follow a modular architecture 
•	Components (AI / DB / Frontend) should be easily replaceable 
7.5 SECURITY
•	API keys must be stored in environment variables (.env) 
•	No secrets should be exposed in the codebase 
7.6 SCALABILITY
•	The system should allow future integration with external data sources 
________________________________________
8. EDGE CASES
EC1 – EMPTY INPUT
If the user submits an empty query → system returns validation message
________________________________________
EC2 – IRRELEVANT QUESTION
If the question is not campus-related → system returns fallback message
________________________________________
EC3 – AI FAILURE
If the AI service fails → system returns user-friendly error
________________________________________
EC4 – LOW CONFIDENCE
If the AI is uncertain → fallback response is returned instead of incorrect information


 

















